.TH SYSINFO 1 "July 2026" "DigiHub" "DigiHub User Manual"
.SH NAME
sysinfo \- display a system and DigiHub status dashboard
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sysinfo
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B sysinfo
prints a summary of the system and the current DigiHub installation:
hardware (on Raspberry Pi), OS/kernel/shell, CPU/memory/disk usage,
network hostname and IP addresses, time and uptime, last login, and
DigiHub's installed callsign, operator, and coordinates (read from
.IR $HOME/.dhinfo ,
if present).
.PP
.B sysinfo
runs automatically at the end of every login shell (it is invoked from
.IR $HOME/.profile ).
If a DigiHub update is available (as detected by the daily
.B dhupdatecheck
timer, or by declining an interactive
.BR dhupdate (1)
run),
.B sysinfo
also shows a one\-line reminder to run
.BR dhupdate .
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Show the current system/DigiHub status:
.B sysinfo
.SH FILES
.TP
.I $HOME/.dhinfo
Read, if present, to display the installed callsign, operator name, and
coordinates.
.TP
.I $HOME/.digihub-update-available
If present, its existence triggers the "Update Available" reminder
line.
.SH "EXIT STATUS"
.TP
.B 0
Displayed successfully.
.TP
.B 1
The shared UI library could not be loaded.
.SH AUTHOR
Steve de Bode \- W0FFS
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR whohami (1),
.BR dhupdate (1)
